work on Gladiator (2000), The Hours (2002) and The Sea Inside (2004).','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2459,'Manolo Garcia','','Manolo Garcia was born in Xativa, Valencia, Comunitat Valenciana, Spain. He is known for his work on Vicky Cristina Barcelona (2008), The Sea Inside (2004) and Biutiful (2010).','','Xativa, Valencia, Comunitat Valenciana, Spain','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2460,'Keith VanderLaan','키쓰 밴더란','Keith VanderLaan is known for his work on Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl (2003), Apocalypto (2006) and Van Helsing (2004).','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,'KeithVanderLaan.jpg'),(2461,'Christien Tinsley','크리스틴 틴슬레이','Christien Tinsley was born in 1974. He is known for his work on I Am Legend (2007), xXx (2002) and The Passion of the Christ (2004).','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,'ChristienTinsley.jpg'),(2462,'Jorge Drexler','조지 드렉슬러','Jorge Drexler was born on September 21, 1964 in Montevideo, Uruguay as Jorge Abner Drexler Prada.','Jorge Abner Drexler Prada','Montevideo, Uruguay','1964-09-21',NULL,NULL,'JorgeDrexler.jpg'),(2463,'Bruno Coulais','브뤼노 쿨레','Bruno Coulais was born on January 13, 1954 in Paris, France. He is known for his work on Coraline (2009), The Chorus (2004) and The Crimson Rivers (2000).','','Paris, France','1954-01-13',NULL,NULL,'BrunoCoulais.jpg'),(2464,'Christophe Barratier','','Christophe Barratier was born on June 17, 1963 in Paris, France. He is a producer and writer, known for The Chorus (2004), Paris 36 (2008) and War of the Buttons (2011).','','Paris, France','1963-06-17',NULL,NULL,'ChristopheBarratier.jpg'),(2465,'Andrew Lloyd Webber','앤드류 로이드 웨버','Andrew Lloyd Webber is arguably the most successful composer of our time. He is best known for stage and film adaptations of his musicals Jesus Christ Superstar (1973), Cats (1994), Evita (1996), and The Phantom of the Opera (2004).\r\n\r\nHe was born on March 22, 1948, in South Kensington in London, England, the first of two sons of William Lloyd Webber, an organist and composer. His mother, Jean Johnstone, was a pianist and violinist. Young Andrew Lloyd Webber learned to play various musical instruments at home and began composing at an early age. He continued his music studies at Westminster School, where his father was an organist. At the age of 9, young Andrew was able to play the organ and assisted his father during performances. In 1964 he went to Oxford University as a Queens Scholar of history.\r\n\r\nIn 1965 he met lyricist Tim Rice and dropped out of school to compose musicals and pop songs. In 1968 he had his first success with the West End production of ‘Joseph and the Amasing Techicolor Dreamcoat‘. From the 1960s to 2000s Lloyd Webber has been constantly updating his style as an eclectic blend of musical genres ranging from classical to rock, pop, and jazz, and with inclusion of electro-acoustic music and choral-like numbers in his musicals.\r\n\r\nAndrew Lloyd Webber shot to fame in 1971 with the opening of his rock opera ‘Jesus Christ Superstar‘. His next successful collaboration with Tim Rice was the musical biopic ‘Evita‘, based on the true story of Eva Peron of Argentina. Andrew Lloyd Webber has been constantly updating the genre of musical theatre. In 1981 he delivered ‘Cats‘, based on Old Possum‘s Book of Practical Cats and other poems by T.S. Eliot. It was produced at New London Theatre, where stage was designed as a giant junkyard with large-scale bottles and cans scattered around a huge tire representing a playground for cats dressed in exotic costumes who would come and go through the aisles. The record-breaking production of ‘Cats‘ was on stage for 21 seasons, from 1981 - 2002, and became one of the most popular musicals of all time. It played the total of 8,949 performances in London and 7,485 in New York.\r\n\r\nIn 1986 Andrew Lloyd Webber released his most successful musical, ‘The Phantom of the Opera‘, based on the eponymous book by Gaston Leroux with the English lyrics by Charles Hart. ‘The Phantom of the Opera‘ became the highest grossing entertainment event of all time, with total worldwide gross of 3,3 billion dollars and attendance of 80 million. It is also the longest running Broadway musical of all time and the most financially successful Broadway show in history. ‘The Phantom of the Opera‘ was translated into several languages and was produced in more than twenty countries as \"clones\" of the original production, using similar staging, direction, costumes concept and sets design.\r\n\r\nHe was knighted Sir Andrew Lloyd Webber in 1992, and was created an honorary life peer in 1997 as Baron Lloyd-Webber, of Syndmonton in the County of Hampshire. He won the 1996 Academy Award for Best Music, Original Song for Evita (1996), and received two more Oscar nominations. Among his other awards are seven Tonys and three Grammys, including his 1986 Grammy Award for Requiem in the category of best classical composition. In 2006 Andrew Lloyd Webber was Awarded Kennedy Center Honors. He owns seven London theatres, which he also restored. Outside of his entertainment career he developed a passion for collecting Pre-Raphaelite paintings and Victorian art. He was married three times and has five children. He is residing in England.\r\n\r\nAndrew Lloyd Webber is currently working on his new opera titled ‘Master and Margarita‘ based on the eponymous novel by Mikhail A. Bulgakov.','','South Kensington, London, England, UK','1948-03-22',NULL,NULL,'AndrewLloydWebber.jpg'),(2466,'Charles Hart','찰리스 하트','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2467,'Glen Ballard','글렌 발라드','Glen Ballard was born on May 1, 1953 in Natchez, Mississippi, USA as Basil Glen Ballard Jr.','Basil Glen Ballard Jr.','Natchez, Mississippi, USA','1953-05-01',NULL,NULL,'GlenBallard.jpg'),(2468,'Alan Silvestri','알란 실버스트리','알란 실버스트리는 세계적으로 유명한 영화 음악가로, 1972년 \"The Boberman Gang\"으로 영화 음악 작업을 시작했다. 그는 주로 로버터 제멕키스 감독과의 작업으로 유명한데, \"로맨싱 스톤(1984년)\"으로 시작해서, \"백 투터 퓨쳐(1985년)\", \"누가 로저 래빗을 모함했나?(1988년)\", \"포레스트 검프(1994년)\", \"콘텍트(1997년)\". \"왓 라이스 비니스(2000년)\", \"캐스트 어웨이(2000년)\", \"폴라 익스프레스(2004년)\", \"베오 울프(2007년)\", \"크리스마스 캐롤(2009년)\"등의 많은 영화에서 작업했다. 그는 \"포레스트 검프\"로 아카데미 영화 음악상을 수상했다.\r\n\r\n그외 많은 블록버스터의 영화 음악 작업으로 유명한데, \"어벤저스(2012년)\", \"캡틴 아메리카: 퍼스트 어벤저(2011년)\", 액션 스릴러 \"프레데터(1987년)\"와 \"어비스(1989년)\", 웨스턴 무비 \"영 건스 2(1990년)\", \"퀵 앤 데드(1995년)\", 어린이를 위한 판타지 \"스튜어트 리틀(1999년)\", \"릴로 & 스티치(2002년)\", \"박물관은 살아있다(2006년)\"의 영화 음악을 맡았다.','Alan Anthony Silvestri','New York City, New York, USA','1950-03-26',NULL,NULL,'AlanSilvestri.jpg'),(2469,'Adam Duritz','','Adam Duritz is an innovative lyricist and piano player who brings the same soul to his friends and lifestyle as he does to the beautiful lyrics and music that he performs. Duritz joined and performed in the Bay area band \"The Himalayans\" until 1991 at which time he left to form Counting Crows. Before he left, however, material was recorded which ...','Adam Frederic Duritz','Baltimore, Maryland, USA','1964-08-01',NULL,NULL,'AdamDuritz.jpg'),(2470,'Charles Gillingham','','','','Torrance, California, USA','1960-01-26',NULL,NULL,''),(2471,'Jim Bogios','','Jim Bogios is an actor, known for Lilith Fair: A Celebration of Women in Music (1997), Sheryl Crow: Rockin‘ the Globe Live (2000) and August and Everything After: Live at Town Hall (2011).','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2472,'David Immergluck','','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2473,'Matthew Malley','','','','Oakland, California, USA','1963-07-04',NULL,NULL,''),(2474,'David Bryson','','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2475,'Dan Vickrey','','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2476,'Tom Hardy','톰 하디','톰 하디는 영국 출신의 배우로, 그는 영국 드라마 센터에서 배우 공부를 했으며, 스티븐 스필버그의 TV 시리즈 \"밴드 오브 브라더스(2001년)\"에 출연했었고, 리들리 스콧의 \"블랙 호크 다운(2001년)\"에도 출연했었다. \r\n\r\n이후 가이 리치 감독의 \"RocknRolla(2008년)\"등의 영화에 출연했지만 크리스토퍼 놀란의 \"인셉션(2010년)\"에 출연하여 세계적으로 유명해 졌다. 이후 그는 \"워리어(2011년)\", \"팅커 테일러 솔저 스파이(2011년)\" 등에 출연했으며, \"다크 나이트 라이즈(2012년)\"에서 크리스토퍼 놀란에 의해 한번 더 발탁되어 베인 역을 맡으며 스타성을 입증 받았다. 그 후