ight.','','Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia','1969-08-21',NULL,NULL,'NathanJones.jpg'),(2482,'Zoe Kravitz','조 크래비츠','Zoe Isabella Kravitz, the daughter of singer/actor Lenny Kravitz and actress Lisa Bonet, was born on December 1, 1988 in Los Angeles, California. She is of half African-American (from her father‘s mother and her mother‘s father) and half Ashkenazi Jewish (from her father‘s father and her mother‘s mother) descent. Zoe‘s love and interest in acting developed from classes she began taking while in school. Wasting little time, Zoe started working on two films during her senior year in high school; No Reservations (2007), directed by Scott Hicks, where she worked alongside Catherine Zeta-Jones and Aaron Eckhart, and The Brave One (2007), directed by Neil Jordan, starring Jodie Foster and Terrence Howard.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, Zoe completed work on Assassination of a High School President (2008), alongside Bruce Willis. She worked with Susan Sarandon and Pierce Brosnan on The Greatest (2009), which debuted at Sundance. Zoe has just wrapped on the latest Joel Schumacher film, Twelve (2010), co-starring Kiefer Sutherland, 50 Cent, Chace Crawford and Emma Roberts, which will be released in 2010. She recently wrapped shooting in New York on her first lead roles in the films, Beware the Gonzo (2010), opposite Amy Sedaris, Campbell Scott and Ezra Miller, and Yelling to the Sky (2011), the story of \"Sweetness O‘Hara\", who has a sometimes-absent father and a present but mentally unstable mother.\r\n\r\nOutside of her film endeavors, Kravitz has kept busy with various projects. She served as lead singer and co-writer with her band, \"Elevator Fight\". Kravitz is also the new face of Vera Wang‘s \"Princess\" perfume. The campaign launches in November 2009. Zoe starred in 2008 in Jay Z music video for his single, \"I Know\", off his \"American Gangster\" album. She was also featured with Jessica Alba, Ryan Phillippe, Tyrese Gibson, George Lopez, John Leguizamo and several other celebrities in Will.i.am‘s \"We Are the Ones\" video during Barack Obama campaign.','Zoe Isabella Kravitz','Los Angeles, California, USA','1988-02-01',NULL,NULL,'ZoeKravitz.jpg'),(2483,'Riley Keough','라일리 코프','Actress and model Riley Keough is the eldest grandchild of legendary singer Elvis Presley and actress Priscilla Presley. Her mother is Lisa Marie Presley and her father is Danny Keough. As a teenager, Keough started modeling. Her first appearance was on a runway for Dolce & Gabbana. She has also appeared on the cover of Vogue with her mother and grandmother.\r\n\r\nKeough‘s acting debut came in 2010 when she won the role of Marie Currie in The Runaways (2010). Other roles followed in The Good Doctor (2011), Jack & Diane (2012) and Steven Soderbergh‘s Magic Mike (2012).','Danielle Riley Keough','Los Angeles, California, USA','1989-05-29',NULL,NULL,'RileyKeough.jpg'),(2484,'Abbey Lee','애비 리','Abbey Lee was born on June 12, 1987 in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia as Abbey Lee Kershaw. She is an actress, known for Mad Max: Fury Road (2015), Ruben Guthrie (2015) and The Victoria‘s Secret Fashion Show (2008).','Abbey Lee Kershaw','Melbourne, Victoria, Australia','1987-06-12',NULL,NULL,'AbbeyLee.jpg'),(2485,'Courtney Eaton','코트니 이튼','Courtney Eaton was born on January 6, 1996 in Bunbury, Western Australia, Australia. She is an actress, known for Mad Max: Fury Road (2015), Gods of Egypt (2016) and Up Close with Carrie Keagan (2007).','','Bunbury, Western Australia, Australia','1996-01-06',NULL,NULL,'CourtneyEaton.jpg'),(2486,'Megan Gale','메간 게일','Megan Gale was born on August 7, 1976 in Perth, Australia. She is a producer and actress, known for Project Runway Australia (2008), Christmas Vacation 2000 (1999) and Body Guards - Guardie del corpo (2000).','','Perth, Australia','1976-08-07',NULL,NULL,'MeganGale.jpg'),(2487,'Richard Carter','리처드 카터','Richard Carter was born on December 11, 1953 in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. He is an actor, known for The Great Gatsby (2013), Mad Max: Fury Road (2015) and Happy Feet (2006). He has been married to Lindsey Carter since February 1, 1991. They have one child.','','Sydney, New South Wales, Australia','1953-12-11',NULL,NULL,'RichardCarter.jpg'),(2488,'iOTA','이오타','iOTA is an Australian singer/songwriter. \r\n\r\nIn 2005 iOTA made his theatrical debut in Hedwig and the Angry Inch. His highly acclaimed performance as Hedwig garnered him a Green Room Award, a Sydney Theatre Critics Award, and a Helpmann Award for Best Male Actor in a Musical.\r\n\r\niOTA then went on to work with Sydney Dance Company on Graeme Murphy‘s Berlin and starred as Frank‘n‘Furter in Richard O‘Brien‘s The Rocky Horror Show, for which he was nominated for a Helpmann Award for Best Male Actor in a Musical.\r\n\r\nHe then co-created the Sydney Festival-commissioned Smoke and Mirrors in 2010, and after a sellout season at the Adelaide Cabaret Festival, Auckland Festival and the Edinburgh Fringe Festival he received three Helpmann Awards for Best Cabaret Artist, Best Original Score and Best New Work.\r\n\r\nSmoke and Mirrors returned to The Sydney Festival in the Famous Speigeltent in 2011 to sell-out crowds followed by another successful season at the Seymour Centre. For the 2012 Sydney Festival iOTA created the show Young, Hard and Solo, performing at the Sydney Opera House.\r\n\r\niOTA has released five critically acclaimed albums, Hip Bone Connection, Little Carlos, Big Grandfather, La Caravana and Beauty Queen of the Sea.\r\n\r\niOTA can be seen in Baz Luhrmann‘s feature film, The Great Gatsby creating the role of Trimalcio - The Orchestra Leader. Most recently he completed filming Fury Road, the fourth of director George Miller‘s Mad Max franchise in the role of Coma - Doof Warrior. A release date isn‘t anticipated until early 2015.','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,'iOTA.jpg'),(2489,'Junkie XL','정키 XL','Junkie XL was born on December 8, 1967 in Lichtenvoorde, Gelderland, Netherlands as Tom Holkenborg.','Tom Holkenborg','Lichtenvoorde, Gelderland, Netherlands','1967-12-08',NULL,NULL,'JunkieXL.jpg'),(2490,'Jan A.P. Kaczmarek','얀 A.P. 카츠마렉','A. P. Kaczmarek is a composer with a tremendous international reputation that continues to grow. As a successful recording artist and touring musician, Jan turned to composing film scores as his primary occupation. Jan‘s first success in the United States came in theater. After composing striking scores for productions at Chicago‘s Goodman Theatre and Los Angeles‘ Mark Taper Forum, Jan won an Obie and a Drama Desk Award for his music for the New York Shakespeare Festival‘s 1992 production of John Ford‘s \"Tis Pity She‘s A Whore,\" directed by JoAnne Akalaitis, starring Val Kilmer and Jeanne Tripplehorn. Newsday wrote that Jan‘s score \"undulates with hypnotic force that gets under your skin,\" while Frank Rich of the New York Times found it worthy of the films of Bernardo Bertolucci and Luchino Visconti. Educated as a lawyer, he abandoned his planned career as a diplomat, for political reasons, to write music in order to finally gain freedom of expression. First he composed for the highly politicized underground theater, and then for a mini-orchestra of his own creation, \"The Orchestra of the Eighth Day\". The major turning point in his life, he says, was a period of intense study with avant-garde theater director, Jerzy Grotowski. \"Playing and composing was like a religion for me,\" Kaczmarek explains, \"and then it became a profession.\" \"The Orchestra of the Eighth Day\" began touring Europe in the late 1970‘s and to date, has completed eighteen major tours. They appeared at the Queen Elizabeth Hall in London, the VPRO Radio International Contemporary Music Festival in Amsterdam,the Venice Biennale, and the International Music Festival in Karlovy Vary, Czechoslovakia, where Jan won the Golden Spring Prize for the Best Composition. He is a five-time winner in Jazz Forum‘s Jazz Top Poll. At the end of the Orchestra‘s first American tour in 1982, Kaczmarek recorded his debut album, Music for the End, for the Chicago-based major independent Flying Fish Records. Jan returned to America in 1989 to find a label for his latest composition for the Orchestra. Jan stayed in the United States where he expanded his horizons by composing for theater as he had already done in Poland with great success, capped by two prestigious New York theater awards in 1992. Having also composed music for films in Poland, he focused his attention to that medium, achieving recognition as a film composer with scores to such films as \"Total Eclipse\", \"Bliss\", \"Washington Square\", \"Aimee & Jaguar\", \"The Third Miracle\", \"Lost Souls\", \"Edges of the Lord\", \"Quo Vadis\" and Adrian Lyne‘s \"Unfaithful.\"','Jan Andrzej Pawel Kaczmarek','Konin, Wielkopolskie, Poland','1953-04-29',NULL,NULL,'JanAPKaczmarek.jpg'),(2491,'John Debney','존 데브니','Academy® Award nominated and Emmy® Award winner John Debney is considered one of the most prolific and successful composers in Hollywood. His unique ability to create memorable work across a variety of genres, as well as his reputation for being remarkably collaborative, have made him the first choice of top level producers and directors.','','Glendale, California, USA','1956-08-18',NULL,NULL,'JohnDebney.jpg'),(2492,'Chris Landreth','크리스 랜드레스','SEE RANK\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChris Landreth (I) \r\n\r\n Director |  Writer |  Animation Department \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n Chris Landreth was born in 1961 in Hartford, Connecticut, USA. He is a director and writer, known for Ryan (2004), The End (1995) and Subconscious Password (2013).','','Hartford, Connecticut, USA','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2493,'Sejong Park','박세종','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2494,'Andrew Gregory','앤드류 그레고리','','','','1900-01-01',NULL,NULL,''),(2495,'Jeff Fowler','제프 파울러','Jeff Fowler was born on July 27, 1978 in Normal, Illinois, USA. He is a director and writer, known for Gopher Broke (2004), A Gentlemen‘s Du